t: Psalm 68
To the chief Musician, A Psalm or Song of David.
Let*p God arise, let his enemies be scattered: let them also that hate him flee before him.
As*p smoke is driven away, so drive them away: as wax melteth before the fire, so let the wicked perish at the presence of God.
But*p let the righteous be glad; let them rejoice before God: yea, let them exceedingly rejoice.
Sing*p unto God, sing praises to his name: extol him that rideth upon the heavens by his name Jah,*s and rejoice before him.
A*p father of the fatherless, and a judge of the widows, is God in his holy habitation.
God*p setteth the solitary in families: he bringeth out those which are bound with chains: but the rebellious dwell in a dry land.
O*p God, when thou wentest forth before thy people, when thou didst march through the wilderness; Selah:
The*p earth shook, the heavens also dropped at the presence of God: even Sinai itself was moved at the presence of God, the God of Israel.
Thou,*p O God, didst send a plentiful rain, whereby thou didst confirm thine inheritance, when it was weary.
Thy*p congregation hath dwelt therein: thou, O God, hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor.
The*p Lord gave the word: great was the company of those that published it.
Kings*p of armies did flee apace: and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.
Though*p ye have lien among the pots, yet shall ye be as the wings of a dove covered with silver, and her feathers with yellow gold.
When*p the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was white as snow in Zalmon.
The*p hill of God is as the hill of Bashan; an high hill as the hill of Bashan.
Why*p leap ye, ye high hills? this is the hill which God desireth to dwell in; yea, the Lord*s will dwell in it for ever.
The*p chariots of God are twenty thousand, even thousands of angels: the Lord is among them, as in Sinai, in the holy place.
Thou*p hast ascended on high, thou hast led captivity captive: thou hast received gifts for men; yea, for the rebellious also, that the Lord*s God might dwell among them.
Blessed*p be the Lord, who daily loadeth us with benefits, even the God of our salvation. Selah.
He*p that is our God is the God of salvation; and unto God*s the Lord belong the issues from death.
But*p God shall wound the head of his enemies, and the hairy scalp of such an one as goeth on still in his trespasses.
The*p Lord said, I will bring again from Bashan, I will bring my people again from the depths of the sea:
That*p thy foot may be dipped in the blood of thine enemies, and the tongue of thy dogs in the same.
They*p have seen thy goings, O God; even the goings of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.
The*p singers went before, the players on instruments followed after; among them were the damsels playing with timbrels.
Bless*p ye God in the congregations, even the Lord, from the fountain of Israel.
There*p is little Benjamin with their ruler, the princes of Judah and their council, the princes of Zebulun, and the princes of Naphtali.
Thy*p God hath commanded thy strength: strengthen, O God, that which thou hast wrought for us.
Because*p of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee.
Rebuke*p the company of spearmen, the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the people, till every one submit himself with pieces of silver: scatter thou the people that delight in war.
Princes*p shall come out of Egypt; Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God.
Sing*p unto God, ye kingdoms of the earth; O sing praises unto the Lord; Selah:
To*p him that rideth upon the heavens of heavens, which were of old; lo, he doth send out his voice, and that a mighty voice.
Ascribe*p ye strength unto God: his excellency is over Israel, and his strength is in the clouds.
O*p God, thou art terrible out of thy holy places: the God of Israel is he that giveth strength and power unto his people. Blessed be God.
